Interview Questions
Q1

Why mock PostgreSQL instead of using the real database?

Answer

A unit test should verify business logic in isolation. Mocking the database keeps tests fast, deterministic, and independent of external systems.

Q2

Why use mockResolvedValueOnce() multiple times?

Answer

bookTicket() executes multiple asynchronous database queries in sequence. Each call needs its own mocked response to simulate the actual execution flow.

Q3

What is the most difficult dependency to mock in this function?

Answer

The PostgreSQL client returned by pool.connect(), because it exposes its own query() and release() methods that are used throughout the transaction.

