🎤 Interview Questions
Q1
Why verify client.query() call count?

Answer:

It ensures the service executed the expected database transaction flow (BEGIN, SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, COMMIT). If a query is skipped or an extra query is added unintentionally, the test will fail.

Q2
Why verify releaseLock()?

Answer:

Locks must always be released, even if an error occurs. Verifying releaseLock() ensures the cleanup logic in the finally block is executed correctly.

Q3
Why verify emit()?

Answer:

Booking success should notify connected clients through Socket.IO. The test confirms that the service triggers this side effect.

