🎤 Interview Questions
Q1

Why use rejects.toThrow()?

Answer

Because bookTicket() returns a rejected Promise when an error occurs. rejects.toThrow() verifies that the Promise rejects with the expected error.

Q2

Why verify that emit() was not called?

Answer

The booking failed, so no success event should be broadcast. Verifying this prevents incorrect side effects.

Q3

Why verify releaseLock() even when the booking fails?

Answer

Locks must always be released to prevent deadlocks and resource starvation. The finally block guarantees cleanup, and the test ensures that behavior.

