🎤 Interview Questions
Q1
Why use Helmet?

Answer

Helmet sets secure HTTP headers that protect against common web vulnerabilities such as clickjacking, MIME sniffing, and some cross-site scripting attacks.

Q2
Why configure CORS instead of allowing "*"?

Answer

Allowing all origins exposes the API to unnecessary risk. Restricting requests to trusted frontend domains improves security.

Q3
Why enable credentials: true?

Answer

It allows browsers to send cookies and authenticated requests (such as Authorization headers) when communicating with trusted origins.



